🔹 BuildMap kya hai (SailPoint IdentityIQ):-
SailPoint IdentityIQ me BuildMap ek utility hai jo key-value pairs (Map) banane ke kaam aata hai — mainly provisioning / rule / connector context me.

👉 Simple language me:-
BuildMap = ek helper jo attributes ko Map format me organize karta hai.

🔹 1️⃣ Map create karta hai:-
BuildMap ka main kaam ek Map banana hota hai:-
Map map = BuildMap.create();
👉 Ye ek empty container bana deta hai jisme data store hoga

🔹 2️⃣ Key-Value data store karta hai:-
map.put("displayName", "Kishan Singh");
map.put("department", "IT");
👉 Data ko key-value pair me store karta hai

🔹 3️⃣ Provisioning attributes prepare karta hai:-
accountRequest.setAttributes(map);
👉 Ye attributes target system (AD, DB etc.) ko bhejne ke liye ready karta hai

🔹 4️⃣ Dynamic data handle karta hai:-
👉 Runtime pe data add / change kar sakte ho:-
map.put("location", "Bihar");
👉 Matlab fixed nahi hai, dynamic hai

🔹 5️⃣ Multiple attributes ek sath manage karta hai:-
👉 Ek hi Map me sab attributes:-
sAMAccountName
mail
department
title
👉 Sab ek jagah store ho jata hai

🔹 6️⃣ Connector ko data pass karta hai:-
👉 BuildMap se banaya hua Map:-
➡️ Connector (AD, LDAP, DB) ko data bhejta hai
➡️ Provisioning ke time use hota hai

🔹 7️⃣ Rule me data organize karta hai:-
👉 BeforeProvisioning / AfterProvisioning me:-
clean data
modify data
validate data
sab Map ke through hota hai.

🔥 Final Summary:-
BuildMap:-
✔ Map create karta hai
✔ Key-value store karta hai
✔ Attributes organize karta hai
✔ Provisioning ke liye data ready karta hai
✔ Dynamic data handle karta hai
✔ Connector ko data pass karta hai.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE Rule PUBLIC "sailpoint.dtd" "sailpoint.dtd">
<Rule language="beanshell" name="Custom-CSV-BuildMap-Rule" type="BuildMap">
  <Description>
    Production Rule: 
    1. Trims all input values to avoid whitespace issues.
    2. Merges 'FirstName' and 'LastName' into 'DisplayName'.
    3. Formats 'TerminationDate' for SailPoint compatibility.
  </Description>
  <Source>
  <![CDATA[
  import sailpoint.connector.Connector;
  import sailpoint.connector.DelimitedFileConnector;
  import java.util.Map;
  import java.text.SimpleDateFormat;
  import java.util.Date;

  // 1. Row data ko map mein convert karna (Default behavior)
  Map map = DelimitedFileConnector.defaultBuildMap(cols, record);

  if (map != null) {
      
      // 2. Data Cleaning: Saare attributes se extra spaces hatana
      for (String key : map.keySet()) {
          Object val = map.get(key);
          if (val instanceof String) {
              map.put(key, ((String) val).trim());
          }
      }

      // 3. Logic: Full Name / Display Name banana
      String fName = (String) map.get("First_Name");
      String lName = (String) map.get("Last_Name");
      if (fName != null && lName != null) {
          map.put("DisplayName", fName + " " + lName);
      }

      // 4. Logic: Date Formatting (Production Standard)
      // CSV Date: 31-12-2025 -> SailPoint Date: 12/31/2025
      String rawDate = (String) map.get("Term_Date");
      if (rawDate != null && !rawDate.isEmpty()) {
          try {
              SimpleDateFormat csvFormat = new SimpleDateFormat("dd-MM-yyyy");
              SimpleDateFormat spFormat = new SimpleDateFormat("MM/dd/yyyy");
              Date dateObj = csvFormat.parse(rawDate);
              map.put("Term_Date", spFormat.format(dateObj));
          } catch (Exception e) {
              // Agar date galat hai toh null set karke aage badho
              map.put("Term_Date", null);
          }
      }

      // 5. Logic: Status Calculation
      String hrStatus = (String) map.get("HR_Code");
      if ("A1".equalsIgnoreCase(hrStatus)) {
          map.put("status", "Active");
      } else {
          map.put("status", "Inactive");
      }
  }

  return map; // Ye map "Resource Object" ban jata hai
  ]]>
  </Source>
</Rule>
